(HASNET PRINTHUB INVESTOR BRIEF) Tj
T*
(Date: April 18, 2026) Tj
T*
(Prepared by: Hasnet ICT Solution \(Project Team\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY) Tj
T*
(Hasnet PrintHub is a smart self-service printing platform designed for kiosk environments) Tj
T*
(\(schools, streets, campuses, offices, and service centers\), where customers can upload) Tj
T*
(documents, pay on mobile money, and print automatically without operator dependency.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The platform is built with a strict business rule:) Tj
T*
(No successful payment means no printing.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This eliminates revenue leakage, improves trust in transaction records, and creates a scalable) Tj
T*
(model for multi-kiosk rollout.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. PROBLEM IT SOLVES) Tj
T*
(Traditional printing points face recurring problems:) Tj
T*
(1. Payment disputes and unpaid prints.) Tj
T*
(2. Heavy operator dependency and inconsistent service.) Tj
T*
(3. Low visibility into daily transactions and printer/device health.) Tj
T*
(4. Difficulty scaling to multiple kiosks with consistent controls.) Tj
T*
(5. Weak audit trail for customer support and operations.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. SOLUTION OVERVIEW) Tj
T*
(Hasnet PrintHub combines:) Tj
T*
(1. Customer flow:) Tj
T*
(Upload PDF -> Quote -> Pay -> Status -> Receipt.) Tj
T*
(2. Mobile money integration:) Tj
T*
(Snippe active now, Mixx ready.) Tj
T*
(3. Automated print dispatch:) Tj
T*
(Print only after payment confirmation.) Tj
T*
(4. Admin operations APIs and dashboard-ready data:) Tj
T*
(devices, payments, incidents, pricing, and daily reports.) Tj
T*
(5. Edge agent on Raspberry Pi:) Tj
T*
(local printer monitoring, queue handling, and job execution.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(4. HOW IT WORKS \(OPERATIONAL FLOW\)) Tj
T*
(1. Customer uploads PDF on kiosk UI.) Tj
T*
(2. System auto-detects page count from uploaded PDF \(not user-entered\).) Tj
T*
(3. Customer selects:) Tj
T*
(   - print mode \(Black & White or Color\),) Tj
T*
(   - copies,) Tj
T*
(   - all pages or custom page range.) Tj
T*
(4. System calculates total cost using server-side pricing logic.) Tj
T*
(5. Customer submits mobile number and name, then payment request is created.) Tj
T*
(6. Payment is reconciled and verified with provider status.) Tj
T*
(7. Only confirmed payment unlocks print dispatch to edge agent.) Tj
T*
(8. Edge agent prints and reports completion back to backend.) Tj
T*
(9. Customer sees final status and receipt details.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
